<div id="pf50e2" class="pf w45 h34f" data-page-no="50e2"><div class="pc pc50e2 w45 h34f"><div class="t m5db x16 he y2f66 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">church went for direction (Acts 1:20); there the great preachers of Acts </div><div class="t m842 x16 he y2e52 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pointed those to whom they witnessed (Acts 3:19-26). </div><div class="t m9e3 x16 h1 y2971 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">VI. WITNESSING TO THE WORLD. </div><div class="t m48b x48 h1 y2983 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m98a x28 h1 y2beb ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Equipped for Witness (Luke 10:1, 2, 16; Acts 11:23, 24). </div><div class="t m202 x48 h1 y1f34 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How has God prepared the way for success to attend our witnessing </div><div class="t m148 x16 h1 y1fed ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">endeavors? Luke 10:18, 19; Rev. 12:9-11. </div><div class="t m791 x48 he y123e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">While the devil still brings woe to the world (Rev. 12:12), God restricts </div><div class="t m715 x71 he ybfd ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his activity in time and authority (Rev. 13:12). Therefore &quot;even the devils </div><div class="t m7c2 x71 he y154e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">are subject unto us through thy name&quot; (Luke 10:17); therefore evil men </div><div class="t me7f x71 he y4dd ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">must stand back from God&apos;s cause (Acts 13:10, 11); therefore those who </div><div class="t m42a x71 he yd38 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">persecute face judgment (Acts 12:23). </div><div class="t m635 x48 h1 y14e7 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Where does our final authority to witness reside? Acts 2:32, 33; Luke </div><div class="t m720 x71 h1 ycd3 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">22:29. </div><div class="t m180 x73 he y821 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;There is nothing that the Saviour desires so much as agents who will </div><div class="t mdc9 x71 he ya90 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">represent to the world His Spirit and His character. There is nothing that the </div><div class="t mb0f x71 he yd74 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">world needs so much as the manifestation through humanity of the Saviour&apos;s </div><div class="t m119 x71 he yf32 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">love. All heaven is waiting for men and women through whom God can </div><div class="t m60f x71 he y669 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reveal the power of Christianity. </div><div class="t madf x1b h21 ydb5 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;â€”The Acts of the Apostles, </div><div class="t m7bf x24 he ydb5 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 600. </div><div class="t mae7 x73 h1 y103b ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m102 x4e h1 y1c17 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Using Every Opportunity (Luke 13:1-5; Acts 26:28, 29). </div><div class="t m1168 x73 he y106e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In Jesus&apos; discussion about faith (Luke 17:5-18:8) He tells us to work </div><div class="t m14e x71 he yf3f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">without expecting praise for our efforts. Doing so gives evidence of faith </div><div class="t m10f x71 he y157e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(17:10). He points to the grateful Samaritan who gave glory to God for what </div><div class="t maa x71 he y15fc ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus had done. Doing so also gives evidence of faith (17:18, 19). </div><div class="t m270 x73 h1 y98b ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What should be our constant concern in a world of uncertainty and </div><div class="t mf49 x71 h1 y1079 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">risk? Luke 13:1-5. </div><div class="t m612 x71 h1 y755 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">VII. ONWARD TO THE WORLD. </div><div class="t m1e2 x73 h1 yd49 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In what spirit should we approach the limitations that health or cir-</div><div class="t m3d5 x71 h1 yc86 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cumstance may place on our ability to witness? Acts 28:20; Luke 23:33, </div><div class="t mac8 x71 h1 y1346 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">43. </div><div class="t m1631 x165 he y23d8 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">95 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0